<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,1755,1932]" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,273,1792,1818]" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">Notes.</emphasis>
Considering that the specimen from Oristano is in fact an 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[973,1310,1793,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Acritus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis" subGenus="Acritus">
<emphasis box="[973,1058,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">Acritus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1076,1160,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">Acritus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1180,1310,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see notes under that species) and that the presence of this species in 
<collectingRegion box="[868,965,1831,1857]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
is neither documented in the literature (Tab. 1) nor confirmed by the study of the various examined collections, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1904" box="[1052,1174,1869,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Acritus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="italicus">
<emphasis box="[1052,1174,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="261">A. italicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is excluded from the Sardinian histerid fauna.
</paragraph>
